<HEADLINE>
GOVERNMENT TO OFFER EMPLOYMENT ASSISTANCE FOR FOREIGN SPOUSES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May  28  (CNA) 05/28/07  20:57:54 (By Luis Huang)
</P>
<P>
A series of employment and vocational assistance activities
targeting foreign and Chinese spouses of Taiwanese citizens will
be held around the country, an official with the Cabinet-level
Veterans Affairs Commission (VAC) announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the activities, which will take place
all over Taiwan, are aimed at helping Taiwanese citizens' spouses
from China and other countries get jobs.
</P>
<P>
The first event will be held Tuesday in the Taipei Youth
Recreation Center under the auspices of the veterans service
offices of Taipei City, Taipei County, Keelung City and Yilan
County, with VAC Chairman Hu Chen-pu presiding, the official
said.
</P>
<P>
The activity will highlight an employment carnival in which 40-50
private businesses and 20 well-known franchised stores have been
invited to offer employment-matching  services and share their
business creation experiences, the official said, adding that
over 1,000 Chinese spouses, retired servicemen and citizens are
expected to attend the event.
</P>
<P>
In addition, experts will also be invited to give lectures on
various employment-related laws and regulations as well as
employment market analyses, according to the official.
</P>
